cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the problem of anomaly detection and classification in distributed systems using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as anomaly detection is a crucial aspect of security. The paper also proposes a novel log preprocessing method and uses deep learning techniques, which makes it relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with distributed systems, which makes it relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
